# A Hybrid Optimizing and Clustering Lung Nodule Malignancy Using Multi-Prototype Attention Capsule Framework

## Overview
This project presents a deep learning-based framework for lung nodule malignancy prediction using CT scan images. The proposed system combines Efficient Capsule Networks, Self-Attention Routing, Multi-Prototype Clustering, and Distribution-Aware Optimization to improve interpretability and prediction accuracy.

## Features
- Lung nodule malignancy prediction
- Self-attention capsule routing
- Multi-centroid prototype clustering
- CT scan image preprocessing
- Explainable AI framework
- Lightweight and efficient architecture

## Technologies Used
- Python
- TensorFlow / PyTorch
- OpenCV
- NumPy
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- Scikit-learn

## Dataset
LIDC-IDRI Dataset

## Project Modules
1. Data Preprocessing
2. Feature Extraction
